race.comment: STYNSY (5) was heavily bet and won a Gold Coast Maiden over 1800m. Appreciate the dryer conditions and he presents fitter. In this lineup the longer journey should hold no fears and he's a chance to take the next step. Metro-trained CHAMPAGNE ROUGE (8) peaks off stronger races and was tracking well before flopping at the Sunshine Coast (vet cleared). Has a wide gate but ran her best race over this distance, and we will see more from her today. HIGH CLASS ROLLER (2) was plain and vet cleared at Ballina a month ago. He's been struggling but showed plenty early doors. Maps well and the switch to Mallyon suggests we'll see improvement. WAKADAISHO (6) won well this track/trip last time, but this looks harder.
